    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "ABOUT PAVE BANK\n\nPave Bank is the world’s first programmable business bank. Built by the founders behind Monzo and BigPay, we’re redefining global business banking by combining programmable financial infrastructure with world-class client experiences.\n\n\nABOUT THE ROLE\n\nPave Bank is building the next generation of programmable banking infrastructure. We’re looking for a Senior Security Engineer who is independent, curious, and has a hacker mindset — someone who thinks like an attacker to keep our platform secure.\n\nIn this role, you will be a critical guardian of Pave Bank, identifying weaknesses, closing loopholes, and empowering our Product and Engineering teams to build and ship quickly without compromising security.\n\n\nWHAT YOU'LL DO\n\n - Review Pave Bank’s platform and product code to identify security issues and guide engineers toward secure solutions.\n\n - Educate engineering and product teams on secure coding and design practices, and why they matter.\n\n - Write and contribute to internal tools, libraries, and automation to improve security testing and enforcement.\n\n - Continuously test internal and external applications for vulnerabilities.\n\n - Stay current on the latest threats and attack techniques, and how they apply to our systems.\n\n - Assist with third-party application security reviews and penetration tests.\n\n\nWHAT YOU’LL BRING\n\n - An adversary-first mindset when approaching software development\n\n - Passion for solving complex security challenges in high-growth startup environments.\n\n - Self-motivation and a desire to keep learning and improving.\n\n - Strong understanding of attacker tools and techniques, and how insecure development practices can be exploited.\n\n - Programming experience in at least one modern language, such as Go, Python, or TypeScript.\n\n - Clear communication skills, with the ability to explain security concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.\n\n - General understanding of blockchain technologies and cryptocurrency systems, and their unique security implications.\n\n\nNICE TO HAVE\n\n - Experience writing secure backend code in Go.\n\n - Familiarity with frontend security concerns in TypeScript-based SPAs.\n\n - Understanding of common authentication and authorization patterns (e.g., OAuth2, Google Zanzibar, RBAC).\n\n - Experience working in security within a fast-paced startup or fintech environment.\n\n - Exposure to smart contract or Web3 security concepts.\n\n\nWHY US?\n\n - We recently raised $39 million in our Series A (led by Accel), positioning the company for major growth and giving you a rare chance to join while things are still moving fast\n\n - Work alongside a founding team from Monzo and BigPay, bringing top-tier fintech expertise to the company.\n\n - Tackle real-world security challenges in a regulated, fast-growing fintech environment.\n\n - Learn from and collaborate with experienced engineers while developing your security career.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
